He also ordered a bigger taxi for us when we left. 

The apartment feels like a house designed by an architect - the owner lives there too! The description is accurate, and it was clean. It's in a safe location close to the metro station, with tons of restaurants right on the street. Overall, staying here was a great decision and good value for the money! If we come back to Barcelona, we'll definitely stay here again.", "Dani's place was awesome. It was super clean, nice and cozy!  The location was perfect, and we got coffee every morning at the cafe. The Crepe restaurant next door had amazing breakfasts too. 

We had a great vacation thanks to Air B&B and Dani!", "Dani was awesome! She showed us around, and the apartment was gorgeous and spotless. It's even better than the pics make it look! The view is incredible too - tons of places to eat and shop within walking distance. Totally recommend!", "The house is in a good location and it's really cozy. The neighborhood is pretty quiet and the rooms facing an inner courtyard are super peaceful. The apartment is spotless and very nicely decorated, with a fully equipped kitchen. Perfect for a short stay. Getting the keys was quick and easy. Highly recommended.", "The house is really nice and well kept, it has everything you need, it's functional and clean. The neighborhood is central and very quiet, even though it's near the Sagrada Familia, which is overrun by tourists. The street is pedestrian only with trees and super quiet, and the house is really peaceful. The living room is very bright, even in the morning, the bedrooms, kitchen, and bathroom have small windows and are not very bright, but that doesn't really matter since we were always out exploring Barcelona all day long. Vika, the girl who welcomed us was super nice and helpful. We loved the house, and the neighborhood and street it's in are adorable, I recommend it!", "This awesome apartment is totally worth it!  Everything was perfect, and super well-equipped. The neighborhood is great with everything you need - a supermarket, bakeries, restaurants, plus the amazing Sagrada Familia and St. Paul's Hospital. It's super close to the metro, so you can get almost anywhere in 30 minutes. We felt right at home!  We highly recommend this apartment.", "Loved the apartment, it was exactly like the photos and super convenient.  It was so cozy and felt like home, I'd definitely stay here again if I ever come back to Barcelona.", 'This place was perfect for a trip to Barcelona, and the host was cool about our arrival and departure times.', "The house is pretty awesome, we all love it! The location is great, and there are restaurants and stores nearby. It's the perfect place for a trip.", "Dani's apartment is central, super close to the Sagrada Familia. 
It has everything you need for a family or friend trip. 
Super well kept, it was the perfect place to explore the city. We'll definitely be back!", "Good location for getting around, with a supermarket, cafe, and restaurants nearby.  We took a taxi to Park Guell that cost €6, which was the same price and faster than the metro. Taxis are cheap in Barcelona. Our neighbors complained about our noise, which could be an issue if you're not as quiet as a mouse. Just me and my teenagers, no parties from our end? Otherwise, it's a good place. Pastries at Choclate Box are delicious.", "The building was super quiet and wasn't on a street with traffic. Everything was close by. It was super clean, modern, and nicely furnished.", 'Flat near Sagrada Familia', 'It was awesome staying at the apartment.  Great location and vibe! Thanks, Dani', "I wanted to thank you guys, Dani and Vika, because we had three awesome days with my family in Barcelona (with baby who is 11 months old).  Dani's apartment is super nice. All the pictures are accurate! The location is really cool - right next to Sagrada Familia and the metro. There are tons of shops around the place too! It's perfect! Thanks, Dani", 'Awesome spot with amazing views of the street and Sagrada Familia!', 'Amazing spot!  5 mins to La Sagrada Familia, easy access to the subway, tons of awesome restaurants.  Lovely place, definitely recommend it!', "The place was even nicer than I thought! It's right next to Sagrada Familia. There are shops and restaurants right downstairs. 

The only thing is, the elevator is a bit of a pain - you have to walk a couple of steps to get to it.", "A really nice apartment, modern and comfy. It's right in the heart of things, just across from the biggest thing in the city - S Familia. Super chill spot but still peaceful.", 'Great spot, good stuff. Check-in was a breeze. Only thing is the elevator starts on the first floor!', "Dani's place is super convenient, right near the Sagrada Familia metro station. It was comfy, and the location is unbeatable. The little balcony with a view of the street life below was awesome! I'd definitely stay here again.", 'The apartment was exactly as described. There were awesome cafes downstairs for breakfast, lunch, and dinner. Sagrada Familia was visible from the balcony, and everything was in a great location. My daughters loved the colors of the apartment and the two beds each. The washer was nice to freshen our clothes on the trip. It was beautifully decorated and felt like a home away from home.', "Awesome place, super clean! It has a great view of a cool street with no cars. It's like two blocks from La Sagrada de Familia and the metro. You can easily get around Barcelona and go to the beach by public transit.", 'Great apartment, just like the listing said and close to public transport, with a view of the Sagrada Familia and a lively neighborhood! The host was super friendly! Would recommend.', "The apartment was perfect for four adults, it had everything we needed and was super clean. We really loved the little balcony with a view of Sagrada Familia and all the street life below. Dani was great to communicate with before our trip; Vika, who stepped in when we arrived, was super helpful and flexible about the check-out time. We'll definitely stay here again!", "This place is awesome! It's a little pricey, but it's super clean and well-maintained. The host is amazing too.", "We had an awesome time in Barcelona. Dani calmed us down about independence stuff, and it was totally chill! The apartment is amazing and super well-equipped, everything's within walking distance (bakeries, little grocery stores, restaurants, the metro station - and of course, Sagrada Familia). There's still so much to see, we'll probably have to come back... 

Thanks a bunch!", 'Cozy, comfortable, charming, well-equipped apartment in a nice neighborhood! We felt very comfortable and safe with our two kids (10 and 12 years old). Lots of shopping and dining options right outside the door, just a few steps to Sagrada Familia and good metro access everywhere from there! Bedrooms are quiet at the back of the apartment.', 'Spacious apartment, super clean and well-kept in Avinguada de Gaudí right in the heart of Barcelona with a view of the Sagrada Familia. Great for families of four. Close to services, the metro is 300 meters away. There are several well-stocked supermarkets nearby. Viktoria and Dani are friendly and kind hosts.', "We loved our trip to Barcelona! Dani's place is even better than it looks in the pictures. The location was awesome, and we had a blast. We would totally come back here if we ever get the chance to go back!", "My wife, daughter, and I stayed at Dani's place for a week. We loved the apartment because of how close it was to Segrada Familia and we could see it from the balcony. We enjoyed lots of coffee sitting on the balcony and admiring it. The Metro is just a short walk down the street and getting around Barcelona's tourist attractions was easy. The apartment is big and the beds were comfy. Dani was really helpful and responsive during our stay. We would definitely come back!", 'A comfy apartment, super well-equipped and two blocks from the Sagrada Familia. Dani was there to welcome us and we had no problems at all.', "We stayed at the house from July 19th to July 27th. The house was in a good location, with bars, restaurants, and markets nearby. There's also the metro and bus stops close by. We had to wait about an hour and a half for check-in because the host was late. The kitchen utensils were dirty, including cups, plates, forks... there was even an electric water heater that was dirty with leftover milk. 
On check-out day, which was at 11am, the cleaning crew arrived at 10:40 am and banged on the door while we were still inside our time limit. We felt like we were being kicked out of the house, everyone waiting for us to leave. It's ridiculous!  Besides these negative experiences, Barcelona was amazing overall.", "Dani's a fantastic host! He dropped off our bags before 2 pm when we got there and picked them up after 11 am when we left. He even gave us an extra towel for the fifth person, which he delivered fast. The place is big enough, in a good location, and a great deal for more than four guests.", "The apartment is really nice and it's right in a great pedestrian area (Avinguda Gaudi) with a gorgeous view of the Sagrada Familia. It's super easy to get around by public transport (the metro and bus are right nearby). There are tons of cafes, restaurants, and supermarkets around the apartment. The apartment has everything you need, including a coffee machine, dishwasher, washing machine, and dryer. If you plan on visiting Barcelona...don't miss it!", "Our family of four (two teenagers) loved our stay! The location was awesome, and there were tons of restaurants and coffee shops nearby that made breakfast and dinner super easy to figure out. The place was clean and modern with a good use of space. We appreciated having two sets of keys which gave us some freedom as a family. Overall, it was an amazing place, well set up and in a great location! We'd definitely come back!", 'This place is awesome, right by everything you need. Super cool and super clean! The hosts were really nice.', "The apartment is in a great location and it's comfy. The amenities are really nice, too. The neighborhood is awesome (right on a pedestrian street).", "This is a great place to stay! The location is awesome, it's a quiet and secure apartment that was super comfy for us and the kids. I would totally recommend booking Dani's place. Thanks so much to him for all his help with our trip. 
Daniel
Melbourne", 'Great apartment close to Sagrada Familia. We traveled with our three kids and were happy with it.

The place was super clean and comfy. Nice beds and lots of space for hanging out. Loved the little balcony to sit on after the kids went to bed. Always fun people watching! Dani had everything we needed for the kids - high chair, crib, a couple toys, even a potty! No bathtub though, just a shower (but he did have an infant tub).

The apartment is on the "first floor" but it's really more like the second or third. There's an elevator but you have to go up a few stairs to get to it which was sometimes annoying with our stroller and kids, but we managed. 

So easy to get to the Metro and hop-on-hop-off bus stops. There are a couple parks on either side of Sagrada Familia great for little ones. The walk to/from Sagrada Familia is full of restaurants and cafes with outdoor seating, shops, markets, etc. I was able to walk a couple blocks to a full service grocery store too. We felt totally comfortable walking back to the apartment at night too. 

Dani was super responsive before we arrived, always answering my emails quickly. Would definitely recommend and stay again.', "Apartment near the metro and Sagrada Familia, just a 5-minute walk. Quiet apartment, but not very bright, with one double bed and one single bed plus an extra bed that can be pulled out, but it's located downstairs. Comfortable bathroom with a great shower but no bidet."]

summary: Trinitat Terrace is a very light and cosy apartment located in Barcelona's district Trinitat Vella, about 30 minutes away from the center of Barcelona. The neighbourhood is residential and, therefore, very quiet. It is a nice area to choose for those who seek a peaceful stay in Barcelona away from the bustle of the city center.
space: The apartment is very comfortable and has 3 bedrooms. One of them features a double bed and the other two - individual beds. One of the individual bedrooms has a balcony. The spacious living room has sofa, TV and a dining area for 4 people. The little kitchen is fully equipped, and the bathroom has a shower. The big advantage of this apartment is its big terrace. It is a great place for a romantic dinner with your loved one or an early breakfast with your roommates before heading to work or university.  Trinitat Terrace is fully-equipped and has all the necessary amenities for your stay in Barcelona. They include WIFI, air-conditioning, washing machine, iron and a dishwasher among others. The apartment can accommodate up to 4 people and is perfect for families and groups of students.

'}, {'_id': '92435161', 'date': '2016-08-08T04:00:00Z', 'listing_id': '2991893', 'reviewer_id': '47947565', 'reviewer_name': 'Jean-Philippe', 'comments': "L'appartement est finalement assez petit par rapport à ce que les photos laissent croire. 

Il faudrait lessiver certains murs qui sont marqués par les passages des voyageurs. 

Il faudrait aussi préciser que l'accès au parking suppose de bien savoir manœuvrer si on a une grande voiture. 

Le quartier est très populaire ! Par forcément très calme. On est réveillé par les bruits de la rue. 

Par ailleurs, il y a des clochards qui dorment dans la rue, sur des bancs mais aussi le long de la porte d'entrée de l'immeuble. Dans l'ascenseur une note du syndic informe que la porte a été forcée à plusieurs reprises ces derniers jours et qu'il faut faire attention à ses affaires et ne laisser entrer personne : ça ne dégage pas des ondes positives. 

Dernier point : sur l'accueil : nous n'avons jamais vu les hôtes mais une personne qui ne parlait pas d'autre langue que l'espagnol (ou la catalan...) et qui s'est contenté de donner reprendre les clefs. Pas très chaleureux. Par contre les hôtes répondent vite par mail. 

Donc, globalement, c'est un petit appartement propret, pas trop mal placé pour l'accès au métro mais dans un quartier qui n'est pas ce que l'annonce laisse croire. 

Un peu trop cher pour ce que c'est (du moins, en pleine saison touristique).

The apartment was exactly as advertised; one of the best we've stayed at on Airbnb.

The kitchen is well-equipped with dishes and cutlery for at least 10 people.

The interiors and furnishings are new and well-kept.

One of the two bedrooms with a double bed is small but if you only use it to sleep, it's not boring.
The bathrooms don't have windows but there's an air purifier.
The only problem we found was that in the evening, with the AC on and several lights on, sometimes the power flickers and we have to systematically reconnect it from the panel behind the entrance door.

Overall, the accommodation is a good choice; I would recommend it. 
Fabrizio", "We stayed in this apartment for four days and it was really nice. Right by La Rambla
Everything's neat and tidy, but there are two rooms with beds that are a little small.

A nice place to stay
I recommend it!
Best regards", "Feels like home away from home. This is our fourth time staying with Alex/Javi and Pilar, and it's been amazing every time! The apartment is always fully stocked with everything we need. They even have extra stuff like water, beer, soda, and cookies. Pilar is so nice and always there to greet us. Check-in and check-out is super easy too. I would definitely recommend this place to everyone.", "Great location! We walked everywhere.  The neighborhood is safe and easy to get around. Our hosts were there on time to check us in. The apartment was a good size for three of us. The only issue was hot water, but we figured that out by splitting shower times between morning and night. Overall, it's a great place right in the heart of Barcelona.", "Spent two nights in Alex's place with a family of five. We drove from Valencia in the minivan and Pilar met us, who doesn't speak English but was super friendly and helpful with tons of local tips. There's secure parking, but it's super tight and not meant for minivans. I managed to get in and out without any damage to the car! The apartment is decent, close to metro stops and good restaurants, especially in Poble-Sec, but going a few blocks into El Raval gets a little sketchy at night so I'd avoid it after dark. It's a pretty easy mile walk to the old town/plaza Catalunya area. The apartment is clean and functional, not luxurious. One bedroom with a big bed, and two smaller bedrooms with beds that can only really sleep one adult/teen. The couch can be used as a bed, but it's not super comfy. Two bathrooms. Washer and dryer are super convenient. Kitchen was nice, and the hosts even left some beers and cokes. There's a small supermarket just two doors down. Alex was good to communicate with and flexible about checkout time for us.  I recommend it!", "Awesome spot! I'd totally recommend it.", 'I liked it! I hope I can come back!', 'Please provide me with the text you would like me to translate! 😊', 'Nice big apartment right in the heart of Barcelona. Pilar was super nice and gave us tons of tips on getting around and what to do. She even helped us find parking in a tiny garage! The place was clean and awesome, we probably went through more Nespresso pods than we should have. The washer and dryer were amazing too.  The apartment had everything we needed!', "Our time in Barcelona was the last stop on our three European cities trip, and it was our third Airbnb stay.  Travel issues made us arrive late at 11pm, but we still got a personal welcome from our host, a tour of the apartment, and free beer, coffee, soda, and advice on seeing the sights in Barcelona. This was a big change from the other two places where we didn't meet our hosts. The apartment was clean, fully equipped, and in a cool, lively neighborhood.", "The apartment is right near the port and not far from La Rambla. There are tons of restaurants and bars nearby.

Javi welcomed us, even though he didn't speak much English, he explained everything and gave us lots of tips on where to go and where to stay away from. We would definitely stay there again.", 'Perfect for tourists. Friendly guests. Fully equipped apartment with secure parking.', "This super clean apartment is perfect for exploring Barcelona. Pilar was waiting for us when we got there, and even though her English and our Spanish/Catalan are limited, we understood everything she told us about the place when we checked in.  There were some nice little things like blackout curtains, a fridge with drinks, a Nespresso machine, and bath gel. The beds are super comfy, you can see a great view from the master bedroom and living room, and the city sounds are muffled so we slept well at night. It was also really helpful to have a washer/dryer. We'd definitely stay here again!", 'We rented an apartment for two nights before our cruise. It was exactly like they said! Super clean, and they even left us some drinks and snacks - that was really nice. Awesome location with a market, bars, and restaurants right around the corner.', "Pilar met us at the front door. The place is super clean, and the beds are comfy. You have almost everything you need for cooking your own meals. There's a grocery store nearby, and the metro station isn't far away. I definitely want to come back!", "This place was awesome! The apartment was super clean, it was right in the middle of everything, and the hosts were really nice. I'd give it a 10 out of 10!", 'We recommend this nice and well-equipped apartment. The only small downside is one of the double beds which is a bit small. The hosts are very responsive and available, and they go above and beyond to provide service.', "The photos are really real and Pilar's service is great.  They also gave us a bunch of drinks and stuff we needed to be comfortable, and they even gave us tips on how to move around better! We're so grateful.", "We had a fantastic time in the apartment. It's not huge but perfect for 4 or 5 people with everything you need. Alex was awesome to communicate with the whole time. Pilar is amazing. What a sweet and helpful lady! We wanted to take her home with us. There are tons of restaurants nearby, the Tapas street was a 10-minute walk, the train station is 5 minutes away, and the Sant Antoni market is just as close. Parking was super important for us, and Pilar helped us find a tight spot in the garage. Everything was safe thanks to her! We appreciated the free beer, coke, and biscuits, and Pilar even paid for our coffees at the cafe below when we arrived early! Not her fault... ours! Nice place, great people.", "This apartment is awesome for families.  They had beer, soda, coffee, and bathroom stuff which was a nice surprise. It's close to La Rambla and Poble-Sec by walking. You can get the metro two blocks away and easily explore the city. There are five grocery stores right around the corner for anything you need. The beds were comfy and the AC worked great.  The washer and dryer were a bonus, they even left pods for us to use. If you're going to Barcelona, this is a great place.", "Traveling with our two sons, this apartment was perfect in so many ways. The space itself was more than enough because each boy had his own room and shared a bathroom. The beds were comfy. The rooms were dark enough for sleeping and the AC worked great. The living area was comfortable too. Having toiletries, coffee, and beer were nice touches and appreciated. The location was awesome – perfect for exploring all of Barcelona's best spots. Las Ramblas is a 10-minute walk, the subway is less than 5 minutes away. Taxis are easy to get one block away. We found out the neighborhood was also super lively and discovered some good restaurants and bars. Great place, great communication, great stay.", "This place was awesome in a newly renovated building. Good elevator, secure doors, nice view from the penthouse. Great AC. The fridge even had some beers, cokes and water. Three grocery stores within a three block radius.

Pilar was super nice when she greeted us. She spent time showing us the whole map of Barcelona. Location was perfect; close to metro stops, 15-20 minute walk to La Rambla. The neighborhood seemed really safe with tons of cool little shops everywhere. We had the best time on Blai St, which is a walking street full of tapas bars about a ten minute walk in Poble Sec. La Tasqueta de Blai! Highly recommend it. Closest metro stop connects right to the Mt Montjuic funicular for a fantastic view of the city and the old castle up there and surrounding parks. To save money, consider riding up and walking down through all the gardens. 

The Passieg de Gracia is where Gaudi's house and Casa Mila are located, and it's a beautiful wide street with tons of cafes. 

Also, the L3 green line is at the closest stop, Paral.lel, and it connects directly to the Airport train for 4.60E. We didn't know the Gay Pride parade was scheduled for 5 PM on the Paral.lel two blocks away. It's entertaining if you're open-minded.", "The apartment is small but nicely furnished with enough room for at least five people. Everything's modern and well-kept, and we loved the kid-friendly dishes and cutlery, plus the fact that there were basic food supplies and thoughtful extras like cold beer and drinks in the fridge.

The place is right next to cool bars and restaurants, and getting around was easy. 

Alex was super nice enough to agree to watch our kids for one evening when we made a last-minute plan to go see JayZ/Beyonce's concert in Barcelona. He also helped with laundry and dishes, which was a huge help! What a treat!

The only thing I would ask future renters who drive is that the parking space in the garage is super tight, and it can be stressful trying to fit our car into the assigned spot. My husband, who's an expert driver, ended up denting our rental car twice while trying to make those turns. 

Overall, a beautiful, sunny apartment with modern amenities and awesome hosts. We'd definitely stay again!", "A great apartment with a lift and drinks and coffee pods waiting for us was awesome! Pilar was super helpful when we arrived early and showed us how everything worked in the place. The beds were comfy, and we all slept well. Our rental car was an Alfa Romeo Stalvio and parking was a pain to get to and got scratched. Also FYI, we went out on the first night and headed right which wasn't so great at night but turning left for dinner the next two nights worked out better.", 'The apartment was exactly as described. Awesome location, easy walk to the town center. The hosts were fantastic, they left some cold drinks in the fridge for us after our long drive.  Communication was great. Free parking on site is a big plus too.', 'Awesome hospitality! Awesome place!', "This is the perfect apartment for a trip to Barcelona! There's parking right with the place, which is safe and secure and you can get to it by elevator from the apartment. Our hosts were awesome, great communication before we got there and then Pilar met us at the apartment to check us in and show us around.

The flat itself is huge and super clean. It has air conditioning, which was a lifesaver (it was 36C when we visited) and the fridge had beer, soda, and milk - such a nice touch!

It's about a 10-15 minute walk from La Rambla, perfect for sightseeing. We would definitely stay here again.", "We really liked this place. The apartment was awesome, super big and comfy with all the stuff we needed.  The AC was a lifesaver! We'd definitely come back and totally recommend it to anyone. Awesome hosts and a great spot.", 'Alex, Pilar and Javi are renting a great apartment with parking in the garage right in the center of Barcelona, just a fifteen-minute walk from La Rambla. Surrounded by tons of restaurants and a newly opened covered market just steps away. The welcome is warm and the explanation of what there is to do is super detailed - awesome! Public transport is also close by. The apartment is neat, with an icebox stocked with beer, water, and soda. Plus, the kitchen has all the amenities you need. The sleeping arrangements are enough for two adults and three kids, but a maximum of four adults. Overall, we highly recommend this apartment!', 'Awesome apartment, fully equipped and functional with parking, perfect for a family in Barcelona!  
We highly recommend it! 
Check-in and check-out are super smooth and flexible.', "We had a great time staying with Alex, Javi, and Pilar! They're super nice and easygoing.  The place is awesome, too. Parking was a huge help since we brought our car. Definitely recommend it!", 'Cozy apartment with parking, great location (20 minutes walk from old Barcelona). Friendly hosts, plus drinks in the fridge! Good wifi. Highly recommend!', 'This place was super clean and well-equipped for our trip. The hosts were awesome and made sure we had drinks and all the stuff we needed. It was a nice bonus! I would totally recommend this place for anyone visiting Barcelona. Thanks again!', "This place is awesome, with cool street views. It's super modern and has everything you need. The hosts were great, making us feel right at home.", "Alex, Javi, and Pilar's place was awesome - big, clean, in a good spot. I got all the info beforehand and met them outside the door. We checked in early which was great! They showed us around the apartment, gave us a map of the city, and told us where to go and what to avoid, which was super helpful! There were some snacks in the fridge too - Coca Cola and beer! We had an amazing time and would definitely recommend this place to anyone visiting Barcelona. Thanks Alex, Javi, and Pilar!", 'Awesome place to stay, close to tons of things to do in Barcelona.  Easy access to three metro stops and super nice hosts!', 'The place was gorgeous, super clean and comfy. They thought of everything to make our stay awesome - from the amazing coffee to extra European plugs for our electronics.  They let us check in way earlier than expected when we got there early in the morning. We had a great time!', "This place was awesome! It was super easy to get to and then easy to get around by walking or public transport. There were tons of restaurants within walking distance too. The place was super clean, spacious, and comfy. Alex met us when we checked in and helped us park the car. Then he showed us a map so we knew how to get to all the places we wanted to see. He was really helpful! Pilar helped us with the car when we left and gave us a warm goodbye. We're so glad we stayed here and would totally recommend it to anyone. Thanks Alex, Javi, and Pilar!!!", "The landlord personally showed us the way when we arrived.  Even though we didn't speak the same language, it didn't stop our communication. He helped us park and gave us a tour of the apartment, explaining its location and nearby attractions. Although the apartment wasn't in the city center, getting around was still easy and safe. So I highly recommend this place! We'll definitely consider staying here again next time.", "Our time with Alex, Javi, and Pilar was awesome!  They were super responsive and it was easy to get in touch. The place was spotless and comfy. They even had coffee, water, soda, and beer stocked - that's a big plus!", 'A cool place, right by the bus stop, La Ramla, and all the other stuff. We never met Javi, but Alex and Pilar were awesome hosts - they answered all our questions fast and helped us out whenever we needed it.', "A cool apartment right in Barcelona, walking distance to tons of stuff and close to the metro if you want to go further. It would be perfect for families or a group of friends traveling.", 'Great location, big place! We loved the location because you can walk or take the subway to everything, but the apartment is on a super quiet street. Pilar met us and gave us some awesome tips on getting around. Highly recommend it!', "This was an awesome place to stay! It was super easy to get around and see everything in the city. The hosts were really nice and helpful.  It's perfect for families because it has three bedrooms and two bathrooms.", "We had a great time! Thanks for the thoughtful gifts.  The free beer, coke and snacks were awesome. Just a heads-up that parking can be tricky for big cars, but Pilar is a pro at finding you a spot. We totally recommend this place when you're in Barcelona.", 'We had a fantastic two-night stay. Pilar is awesome and knows all the best spots to check out. The apartment is super convenient!', 'Pilar was really nice! The apartment matched the description and is in a great location.', "Awesome apartment in the heart of Barcelona, close to metro lines, restaurants, supermarkets, excellent location and a very quiet and safe neighborhood. The place is perfect for families with kids, and they're really flexible!", 'Awesome!', 'Nice stay in this apartment', 'Clean and nice apartment, comfortable with parking. The nearest tube, Universitad, is only five minutes walk away, and connects you to Spain Square and more, via the red line. neighborhood_overview: You couldn't be better located. The apartment is located in Eixample, the most iconic neighbourhood in the centre of Barcelona. You will be located in an charming area with the best of Barcelona’s modernism alongside elegant shops and boutiques. Main landmarks include Gaudi’s awe-inspiring Sagrada Familia and Plaza Catalunya, where shopaholics will find an array of commercial chains and boutiques offering all the latest trends.  You’ll have plenty of opportunities to try some typical Spanish and Catalonian gastronomy in the restaurants which populate the area. They include the revered Teoric Taverna Gastronomica, where gleaming reviews are proof of the high quality Mediterranean dishes on offer and Don Kilo Barcelona, an extremely popular restaurant serving Italian classics.  This neighbourhood is well-connected to the main city attractions and offers great public transport connections, so enjoy the area knowing that other exciting Barcelona neighbourhoods are within easy reach!
notes: According to the Law, you will be asked at the moment of the check-in for your IDs. Hope this is not an inconvenience.  In the building, there will be some apartments making some minor refurbishments, you might find some disturbances because of this. We apologize in advance for this.
transit: Universitat is the nearest station to the apartment, just a five minutes walk away down to Gran Via, which is a main street in the city that will lead to Plaza Catalunya. This connects you to the L1 - red line, meaning you can get to iconic Barcelona sites in no time at all, such as Plaza España (Spain Square), The Sagrada Familia Temple, Las Ramblas or the many beaches in Barcelona. There are also plenty of buses such as V9 that stop just down the street that will take you all over the city and you can make connections to lovely places, such as Mount Tibidabo, the Acquarium or The Casttle in Mountjuic.  Exploring all of the attractions of Barcelona could hardly be easier!

space: High-standing apartments, located in L'Eixample of Barcelona, surrounded by numerous and varied shops and restaurants. The building is just 5 minutes walk from Plaza Catalunya. Air-conditioned apartment with 1 double bedroom with TV and 1 bedroom with 2 single beds. Each room has a private bathroom with a hairdryer and free toiletries. The kitchen is equipped with oven, microwave, dishwasher, fridge, cooking utensils, and a washer-dryer machine. The lounge has satellite TV and free Wi-Fi. This spacious apartment with marble floors is an ideal choice for 4 people. The property has parking for vehicles (depending on occupancy), available for an additional charge. name: Studio 12 square meters(penthouse)
summary: Studio well connected to subway, bus and Sants Station. 12 square meters overlooking Montjuïc, very sunny (it’s a penthouse). It has a community terrace for sunbathing. There are: kitchen, washing machine, Air Conditioning, Wifi and elevator.
space: - The studio is small but allows full independence since spaces are not shared with anyone (except communal terrace). - Only for one person. Not fit 2. - Single Bed 190x90 cm (spring mattress). - The communal terrace, usually not frequented by neighbours. - It is not a noisy place. South orientation. - What you will find in there? . In the kitchen you will find: microwave, Kettle, coffee/tea manual maker, dishes, glasses, cutlery, fridge (quieter than previous), cooking pots, bottle opener, corkscrew, can opener, dish soap, scourer, ... . In the bathroom you will find: towels, shower gel, shampoo, laundry detergent, washing machine and toilet paper. . In the bed you will find sheets and blanket in winter season. . The studio has air conditioning. . In case you need to feel more comfortable, you will find cleaners for dust, fat, glasses and floor. Also there are bleach to disinfect (I have never had a complaint about cleanliness) . There is no food and drinks.

The studio has air conditioning.
neighborhood_overview: Sant's neighbourhood is well connected, cheap and with many services. The fresh Market of Sants neighbourhood is to 5 minutes from the studio. In the same street of the studio, you can find grocery store, one supermarket, and 3 o 4 bars to eat. Two minutes walk, you find Sants Street, a four kilometers followed by trade, both sides of street, with more than three hundred shops and service establishments. The Saints Street, is undoubtedly the longest shopping street in Europe.
notes: - Wifi: optical fiber (download 30 Mbps; upload 30 Mbps) shared with the host. - Electricity: 7,42 kwh per day is included in the price and it is enough for a normal use. If you need more electricity, you should pay 0,27 euros per kwh in the prepaid electric meter. You can see, at any time, your credit for electricity in a display in order to avoid the electricity cut. The property is not liable for damage caused by power cuts. - Water and Wifi are included in the price. - There is not cleaning service while you live in the loft. Of course, when you arrive first time, you will find the loft cleaned.
transit: 2 minutes from the loft you can find the blue subway line (L5) and red line (L1), Sants Square stop. A 8-minute walk, Sants Station with multiple connections to subway, bus, train and high speed train (which is called AVE)
access: The guest have access to all can be seen in the pictures: loft of 12 square meters and the community terrace.
interaction: The owner lives in a flat next to the Studio, so you can interact with host when you need and if not, you will meet him when you check in and when you check out.
house_rules: Please do not cause inconvenience to other neighbors or organize parties on the terrace.  Smoking is not allowed inside the studio. You can smoke in the communal terrace (please do not throw cigarettes on the ground). The Studio is only for one person. If you have the idea to accommodate 2 or more persons during your stay, without the permission of the host, reservation will be cancelled for reasons of space, hygiene and noise. No pets allowed.

comments_traducidos:
["Friendly owner Jordi showed me the apartment and neighborhood. The location is super convenient - right next to the metro and train station. Getting from the airport is quick. You can get to the city center by metro. There are tons of cafes and shops nearby. The apartment is small, but perfect for one person. It has everything you need - a mini kitchen, washing machine, good internet, towels. Plus there's a spacious terrace with a great view. A fantastic deal for the price!", "Jordi is a really nice and helpful host. He even let me borrow his hairdryer for the whole time I stayed there haha. The mini apartment is on the top floor of an old building, you get up there by elevator. It's fully equipped, clean and simple. There's a balcony with a great view of Barcelona from it. You can even see the Royal Palace! 

The neighborhood is really cute and well-kept, lively, full of people, cafes, restaurants, shops, and services. It's very easy to get to the city center by metro (the station is just a 2 minute walk away) and there's also a train station nearby (website hidden). I had a great time!

Definitely recommend it. Thanks Jordi, hope to see you soon!", 'Jordi was a really good host, super friendly and welcoming. The apartment and the neighborhood (Sants) in Barcelona were perfect for a solo traveler. Everything was well organized and the communication before the trip was great. The apartment and the terrace are perfect for a stay in Barcelona. Wifi was awesome and Jordi took great care! Thanks! Highly recommend it!', "I had an awesome time at Jordi's place. The studio was way better than I expected, super clean, quiet, in a great location that was easy to get around, and had everything I needed. Amazing views and a nice breeze. The kitchen was pretty bare, but I managed just fine cooking there.  The bed could be more comfy, but a mattress pad would fix that. The apartment stayed warm when I was there in August, but the fan definitely helped!", 'It was a cozy little place, perfect for one person.', "Jordi's place is perfect for solo travelers wanting to explore Barcelona. It's quiet and super convenient with a market and a fresh fruit/veggie store right around the corner. The apartment itself is small, but just right for one person. It's clean, has an elevator, and there's a little patio right outside your door. Plus, Jordi lives right next door, so it's easy to ask him any questions you might have. Thanks again, Jordi!", "This place is super convenient, and even though the apartment is small, it's really well-designed!  I was happy there was an elevator too (because my luggage was heavy). Met Jordi when I arrived and we actually had some good chats while I was there. He was always helpful if I needed info.", "I miss my perfect little penthouse! 

It's a bright, clean apartment. Yeah, it's small, only big enough for one (perfect for one!), but there's actually plenty of room because Jordi designed it so well that not an inch is wasted. There's tons of storage too. You'll have everything you need there. Plenty of hot water, super fast wifi (that even works on the terrace), fridge, microwave, cooking hobs, and washing machine. There are pull-out tables too which I found really useful. It's on the top floor (with a lift - yay!) and it's really quiet. One of my favorite things was the huge terrace. It was sunny during the day and had a nice breeze in the evening. And there are great views too - over the rooftops and into the city and the mountain range. Jordi lives across the hall so it was handy to have him nearby. Jordi is a great host. I had cold drinks waiting for me when I arrived and Jordi gave me a good introduction to the city and things to do and helped get me oriented. He's happy to share his knowledge and he's really helpful and friendly, and a great neighbor too! Great location with the bus and metro right at the end of the street. There are tons of little local shops right on the same street with a fabulous food hall (hot food, meat, fish, fruit, veg) a few minutes walk away and next to a big supermarket. Plus there are lots of other shops nearby too! I walked into the city and it took me about 50 minutes to La Ramblas so if you want to take a stroll, it's walkable to the city. It's in a great location in a residential neighborhood and I felt very safe on the streets day and night. Less is definitely more with this penthouse and I am so glad I made this choice and recommend you do too! Jordi - thanks again for everything and I hope to be back soon!", "Jordi emailed me directions to his place so I got there without any trouble. His apartment is across the hall which was nice. Jordi was really helpful answering my questions about where to get things in the neighborhood and about the culture. He made a map showing some shops, restaurants, and parks. I enjoyed our chats a lot. If I ever go back to Barcelona, I'd stay at Jordi's place.", 'Amazing host, awesome communication! He was super helpful and flexible with my arrival time.

Loved my stay!', "Jordi's a good guy and super helpful.

I like Jordi's place.", "I spent a week in Jordi's small but cute apartment. It was perfect if you like a cozy space. It's light, clean, and really nice. It has everything you need, whether you want to cook or eat out.

name: Eric Vökel Boutique Apartments - Sagrada Familia Suites - 2 Bedroom 2 Bathrooms Apartment
space: This beautiful early 20th century modernist property is located right next to Avinguda Gaudí and just 200 meters from the Sagrada Família.  The building includes 17 spacious apartments which were completely refurbished from the hand of Eric Vökel. Furthermore, it is located in Barcelona's Eixample neighborhood, next to all types of retail stores and dozens of eating terraces for either lunch or dinner. The metro station is right on the corner and connects you to any point of the city. Large 70m2 apartment with two double bedrooms and two bathrooms, one of which is en-suite to the master bedroom. It also has a living room with a fully equipped kitchen and a balcony. Ideal for unforgettable moments spent in great company. Total sleeping capacity: 6 people (double sofa bed for 2 guest) For stays of 4 nights or more, there is a cleaning service every 4 days. Additional cleaning services can be booked at an extra cost.  Apartments include bed linen and towels.

name: Pulitzer Extra- Read all about our experiences!
space: One day a guest said to us, “The Pulitzer is a happening place. I love it!” And that is exactly what it is. Far from being a collection of rooms, the Pulitzer is a place with a pulse, where there are always things happening, where every day is different. It is decidedly ‘cool’: a destination in its own right. The Pulitzer is a boutique hotel located right in the heart of Barcelona, a stone’s throw from Plaza Catalunya. Its unforgettable location is one of its main points of appeal as it is surrounded by the best cultural attractions, the most exclusive shopping, the most important business centres and is at the hub of the entire urban transport network.

name: Room “Elegance” in Barcelona centrum.
summary: Preciosa habitación privada y equipada en mi bonito apartamento, acogedor y elegante en la quinta planta de un edificio con ascensor en el conocido y vivo barrio de l’Eixample de Barcelona.  Cama doble, con un colchón y almohadas de alta gama de viscolatex, decorada al detalle, tiene 2 ventanas que dan al interior del edificio, pero silencio garantizado.  Estaré encantada de recibirles con los brazos abiertos, sólo pido que sean personas serias y respetuosas y que cuiden de mi casa.
space: Mi apartamento está situado en el barrio de L’Eixample, uno de los barrios más céntricos y conocidos de la cuidad, famoso por su movimiento constante de gente, sus restaurantes, bares, tiendas, y todo lo que todo el mundo necesita tener siempre cerca o a mano.  En mi apartamento solo vivo yo, por lo que no tendrás que compartir baño o cocina con más gente que conmigo. La habitación es preciosa, muy acogedora y decorada al detalle para que tú estancia en la cuidad sea inolvidable. Te ofreceré sábanas, toallas, perchas, mesita en la habitación, wifi, baño compartido conmigo, gel, champú, lavadora, cocina, utensilios, desayuno, wifi y estaré a tu disposición para lo que necesites, siempre y cuando esté a mi alcance.  La habitación es muy fresca en verano, el apartamento dispone de aire acondicionado, en invierno con el edredón es suficiente.

neighborhood_overview: EN EL BARRIO Zona muy céntrica con muchos Bares, Restaurantes. Recomiendo sobre todo la calle Parlament, que está muy de moda para desayunar, tomar algo o cenar unas tapas. Podéis encontrar todo tipo de restaurantes muy cerca de casa, para todos los gustos y presupuestos: tailandesa, española, persa, italiana, pizza al taglio, cafeterías, librerías/cafeterias, mexicano, tapas… Justo debajo de casa hay un supermercado que abre de lunes a domingo hasta las 23h. También hay una farmacia que cierra a las 23h todos los días. QUÉ VISITAR: Cerca se encuentran los principales puntos turísticos como las Ramblas, el museo MACBA, el Raval, el mercado de la Boquería, las fuentes mágicas de Montjuic, la playa... Hay muchos bares y tiendas en los alrededores. Las estaciones de metro más cercanas son Rocafort (L1 - roja), Urgel (L1 - roja), Sant Antoni (L2 - lila) y Poble Sec (L3 - verde). Y un bus directo al aeropuerto que pasa debajo de casa, el Aerobús. A la playa hay un paseo andando de 30 minuto
notes: CHECK IN Y CHECK OUT: - El check-in es muy flexible, hay que informar SIEMPRE con anterioridad de vuestra hora de llegada. Si queréis entrar tarde, a partir de las 22h, no hay problema, siempre que se consulte primero. Si queréis entrar antes de las 16h, avisadme y haré todo lo posible por conseguirlo. Si no se puede, siempre podéis venir a dejar vuestras maletas en mi piso. - Si se quiere hacer un late Check out (salir más tarde) hay que avisar con anterioridad, y dependerá de la disponibilidad. Tal vez se puedan dejar las maletas y venir más tarde a por ellas, pero siempre hay que preguntar primero, si no el check out es como muy tarde a la 13h. NORMAS - Si se ensucian mucho las sabanas o toallas, se descontarán 15€ por cada sabana y 5€ por cada toalla. Si dejas las toallas negras o muy manchadas de maquillaje... se te aplicará este coste extra a través de Airbnb. - Cuida todo como si fuera tuyo.  - Apagar SIEMPRE el Aire Acondicionado y luces al salir. - Cuidado con el ruido en las
transit: TRANSPORTE: Se puede ir andando a gran parte de las atracciones interesantes de la ciudad. Metro y Bus a unos metros. El aerobús para ir al aeropuerto para a 30 metros de casa. La parada de metro más cercana es Rocafort (L1 - roja), Urgel (L1 - roja), Sant Antoni (L2 - lila) y Poble Sec (L3 - verde). Aunque también hay multitud de autobuses cerca como el H-16 etc. Lo más cómodo es usar la aplicación G.Maps, que funciona muy bien para manejarse en la ciudad.

Clothes shopping is also a pleasure in El Raval thanks to the little one-off boutiques that line some of the streets giving you a truly unique shopping experience. Unlike the Eixample with its large branded name designer labels, Raval is where you find the small privately owned shops selling clothes you can't find anywhere else.
